			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Melee while twisting<a name="17357"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 27 04 7:53 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Simply turn on auto-attack and have at.  Twist your songs, and the game will work a blow in when it needs to without interupting the song.  Your hand-to-hand skill will rise until you:  A.  get dual wield at 17 and get primary hand instruments; or B.  learn to rapidly switch instruments and weapons.  
<br />

<br />
All of our songs pretty much have the same duration.  3 seconds to cast and 18 seconds effect.  In theory, we should be able to keep 6 songs going but in practice, 3 is about all we can reliably manage.  This is because of network delays, human reaction times, game delays (lag), and individual computers.  Practice, read the guides on this site about twisting, practice, read the guides on various forms of kiting (you don't have the songs to do them yet, but the techniques can be adapted), and practice some more.
<br />

<br />
Check out the UI boards.  There are some that display your inventory slots next to your hot key bank and even put your primary and secondary weapon slots there.  There are a couple that put those slots on every bag you open.  (I use the container window from www.sarshasit.com myself.)  This is INVALUABLE for instrument/weapon swapping!  With most of our songs, you do NOT have to have the instrument in hand after the effect starts, or even when you start the song.  It only has to be there when you end the casting.  
<br />

<br />
Get some ice packs for your wrists and have fun.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
